insert into CET6WordBook values ('186', 'burglar', '[bɝɡlɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=burglar', '{n.}++夜盗，(夜间破门入室的)盗窃**++窃贼，贼，小偷，破门入室偷窃者**{vt.}++盗窃，偷盗，偷窃(某物)；抢劫(某处)；进行盗窃(或偷窃)**', '++The Police arrested the burglar.**++警察逮捕了窃贼。**++The detective took out after a burglar.**++那侦探追赶一个窃贼。**++It earlier quoted the store@s owner saying the burglar always cleaned up after himself, but the dolls were dumped unceremoniously in an alleyway behind the store.**++早先引用商店老板的话说，这个窃贼在完事之后，总会把现场清理干净，但是，充气娃娃会被随便扔到商店后门的过道上。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('187', 'burial', '[bɛrɪəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=burial', '{n.}++葬(水葬或土葬)，埋葬；掩埋**++葬礼**++坟墓，坟地，葬地，墓地**++丢弃，丢掉，弃绝**{adj.}++埋葬的，葬的**++葬礼的**', '++One of the first things they noticed is that Deuteronomy 34 describes the death and burial of Moses.**++其中第一个便是，他们注意到在《申命记》34中4,描述了摩西死亡以及葬礼。**++So if you want to become part of the dirt you will go into, consider a simpler and closer to nature way of burial.**++所以，如果你想成为你将融入的泥土的一部分，那你可以考虑一种更简单的、更接近自然的埋葬方式。**++A thousand pounds of metal is an enormous amount of wealth in this era. To waste so much of it in a burial is pretty unusual.**++在那个时代，一千磅的金属材料是一笔数额巨大的财富，耗费这么多的材料用来埋葬是相当不寻常的。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('188', 'burner', '[bɝnɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=burner', '{n.}++炉膛；煤气头；灯头**++炉子；火葬室**++燃烧器，灯；喷灯，喷烧器**++(喷气引擎的)燃烧室**++烧者，以烧某物为职业者；烧制者**++燃烧物**', '++He says: "It’s like an old charcoal burner. The coffee is heated up like charcoal.**++他说：“这就像古老的木炭燃烧器，咖啡在这里就像木炭一样被加热。**++An electric field pushes a flame away from a burner in a recent Harvard experiment.**++在哈佛的一项近期实验中，一个电场把火焰从燃烧器上推开。**++Then the remaining transuranics would be transferred to a burner to be fissioned into more stable materials.**++然后其余的铀后元素被转移到燃烧炉中裂变为更稳定的材料。**');
