insert into CET6WordBook values ('823', 'hemisphere', '[hɛmɪsfɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hemisphere', '{n.}++(地球或天体的)半球**++半球上的国家**++半球上的居民**++半球地图**++半球，半球体**++(生活、活动、思想、知识等的)范围，领域**++【解剖学】**++大脑半球**++小脑半球 (=cerebral hemisphere)  [参较 Eastern Hemisphere, Western Hemisphere, Northern Hemisphere, Southern Hemisphere]**', '++It is further divided into four regions, or lobes, in each hemisphere.**++每个半球它又进一步分化为四个区域或四个脑叶。**++Because language centers are smaller, and only located in one hemisphere, this puts males more at risk for language disorders like dyslexia.**++因为语言中心更小，只位于一个半球，这也使男性陷入如失语症等语言紊乱的危险中。**++If jobs require people to commute a great distance or to move themselves to another state, or to another hemisphere, employers may find they need to sweeten their offers.**++如果提供的工作要求雇员通勤很长的距离或者搬家到另一个州或另一个半球，那么雇主则会发觉他们应该提供更丰厚的待遇。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('824', 'henceforth', '[,hɛnsfɔrθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=henceforth', '{adv.}', '++The sad gangsters said that they would not do it henceforth.**++沮丧的绑匪说他们今后再也不干这种事了。**++Its contribution henceforth, the official said, should be “harmony”.**++这位官员说，从今以后，它的贡献就是“和谐”。**++Henceforth, each date in the studio would involve dedicated work on a couple of tunes, after which the band would disappear to learn the next few songs.**++自此以后，在录音室里的每一天都将对许多曲子进行精心的加工，随后乐队成员都将消失去学习另外一些歌曲。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('825', 'herald', '[hɛrəld]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=herald', '{n.}++(旧时)皇家信使；传令官，(比武大会等的)宣令调度官；掌礼官；使节**++报信者；使者**++通报者，报道者**++预告者，预报者；先驱，前锋**++预兆，先兆**++【英国历史】司宗谱纹章的官员**{vt.}++预告；宣布，报告…的消息：**++引进；引领：**++为…欢呼；欢迎：**', '++He was assembling a complication that sent a little gilded boy with a trumpet through a door in the clock face to herald the birthdays of its owner@s family.**++他正在组装一个复杂的钟，这个钟里面要安装一个镀金的小男孩，手里拿着一支小号，从钟面上的一扇门出来，通报主人家人的生日。**++While working as a secretary for the publisher of Washington State@s Inland Herald, she criticized his prose so vocally that he replaced her and made her an editorial writer instead.**++在身为秘书，替华盛顿州的内陆先驱出版社的出版商工作时，她直言不讳的批判了他的散文，以至于他调动了她的工作，干脆让她去做社论了。**++The New York Herald, meanwhile, proposed that the federal government should wait until the war ended and sell all the slaves back to their owners, at half-price, to finance its cost.**++纽约先驱报在当时也建议联邦政府应该等到战争结束，然后把这些奴隶再卖会给他们的主人，可以半价出售来支持其战争成本。**');
