insert into CET6WordBook values ('1102', 'measurement', '[mɛʒɚmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=measurement', '{n.}++测量；计量；丈量；量测**++测量法**++测量的结果；(量得的)尺寸；大小；长(或宽、高)度；面积；容积**++量度制；量测方法**++[复数][口语](妇女的)三围(指胸围、腰围和臀围)**', '++In this example, the component itself provides the measurement.**++在这个例子中，组件本身提供了度量。**++If we think about the What, How, Who, and measurement of the standard IT project, we see that these functional attributes are not always well defined either.**++如果我们考虑标准 IT 项目的这四个方面（什么、如何、谁和度量），就会发现不一定总是定义了这些功能性属性。**++I mentioned throughput and how page rate provides a consistent measurement for many of the performance tests that you will run.**++我前面提到了吞吐量和页面速率如何为您将要运行的许多性能测试提供一致的度量。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1103', 'mechanics', '[məkænɪks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mechanics', '{n.}++[复数]**++[动词用单数]力学；机械学**++[用作复数](机械等)结构；构成**++[用作复数]技术性细节；例行手续；例行方法**', '++But it does happen in quantum mechanics.**++但它在量子力学中就发生了。**++He set up in that way an alternative form of quantum mechanics.**++他就是以这样一种方式建立了量子力学的另一种形式。**++In this example we exploited the quantum mechanics principle of superposition.**++本例中，我们利用了量子力学的叠加原理。**');
