insert into CET6WordBook values ('1121', 'microprocessor', '[,maɪkroprosɛsɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=microprocessor', '{n.}', '++Our applications take in massive amounts of information and crunch it with the power of the microprocessor.**++我们的应用程序将接收大量信息并使用微处理器的能力来处理这些信息。**++Anything that has a microprocessor in it has support for C. From your microwave to your cell phone, C powers technology.**++任何带有微处理器的东西都支持C。 从你的微波炉到手机，C 提供强大的技术动力。**++Typically, these devices run a 32-bit microprocessor/controller and have more than 2 MB of total memory for the storage of the virtual machine and libraries.**++典型地，这些设备运行一个 32 位的微处理器／控制器，而且有总量大于 2 MB 的用于虚拟机和库的存储的存储器。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1122', 'microscopic', '[,maɪkrəskɑpɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=microscopic', '{adj.}++用显微镜可见的；微小的；细小的；微观的；极小的**++显微镜的；用显微镜的**++显微镜似的；任何细节都不放过的**++与显微镜使用(或检查)有关的 [亦作 microscopical, 参较 macroscopic]**', '++It@s the electricity formed, for instance, when water vapor collects on microscopic particles of dust and other material in the air.**++具体地说，空气中的电流是水蒸气在悬浮于空气中的灰尘和别的微观粒子中聚集时形成的。**++All the microscopic available states, that is, if I take an individual particle and I say where it can be, all those states have the same energy.**++所有的微观的可能的状态，也就是，如果我以一个单独的粒子为例,我说它可能在哪，所有那些状态都有相同的能量。**++Although still a long way off, the team suggests these biological logic gates could one day form the building blocks in microscopic biological computers.**++尽管仍然有很长的一段路要走，研究小组提出，这些生物“逻辑门”有一天能在微观生物电脑中构建建筑模组。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1123', 'microwave', '[maɪkrəwev]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=microwave', '{n.}++微波**{adj.}++微波的**{vt.}++放入微波炉烹调(或加热)食物：**++放入微波炉烹调(或加热)食物：**{vi.}++用微波炉烹调：**++用微波炉烹调：**{abbr.}', '++Never microwave egg in the shell.**++勿将带壳的鸡蛋放入微波炉内加热。**++These variations caused minute differences in the temperature of the early universe, which we can see in the cosmic microwave background.**++这些变化导致早期宇宙的温度瞬间不同，这些我们能在宇宙的微波背景上看出来。**++One possible explanation is that the universe is small - so small that, back when the microwave background was being produced, it just could not hold those big blobs.**++一个可能的解释，宇宙是微小的——它是如此微小，以致如果回到微波背景刚刚产生时，它不可能容纳大的泡泡。**');
