insert into CET6WordBook values ('1528', 'remainder', '[rɪmendɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remainder', '{n.}++剩下的人；其余的人**++剩余物；残留部分；遗物；遗迹**++(因滞销而减价出售的)存书；处理书**++(已停止使用的)过时邮票**++【法律】剩余财产；剩余财产继承权；房地产的指定继承权；爵位继承权**++【数学】差数；余数；余额**{adj.}++[罕用语]剩余的**{vt.}++减价出售(书籍等)；削价处理(存货等)：**++减价出售(书籍等)；削价处理(存货等)：**', '++The remainder of this section introduces those models.**++本章节的剩余内容介绍了这些模型。**++The remainder of this article examines the second type of issue, which can be an annoyance for readers.**++本文剩余内容将探讨第二种类型的问题，这些可能是读者非常厌烦的问题。**++If the first character of a command is a hyphen (-), the remainder of the line is executed, but its exit status is ignored.**++如果一个命令的第一个字符是连字符（-），那么该行中剩余的命令都会执行，不过其退出状态会被忽略。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1529', 'repay', '[ripɛi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repay', '{vt.}++偿还(钱款或债务)；归还(某人)：**++报答；回报；报复：**++补偿；偿付：**++值得，应得**{vi.}++偿还；补偿；报答**++报应；惩罚:**', '++She engaged herself to repay her debt within two months.**++她答应在两个月内偿还她的债务。**++They are under to obligation to repay debts incurred by the old regime.**++他们没有偿还旧债的义务。**++We should repay his kindness.**++我们应该报答他的好意。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1530', 'repeal', '[rɪpil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repeal', '{vt.}++撤销；废止：**++[废语](从流放地)召回**++放弃；拒绝承认**{n.}++撤销；废除**++[废语]召回**', '++In some states, the centralization of districts into towns went through waves of passage and repeal.**++而在有些州，将区并入城镇的努力也经历了通过与废除相互交织的多舛命运。**++Therefore, he said, a committee of top officials would work to repeal the report and minimize "the great damage" it has done to the state of Israel.**++所以他说，一个由高级官员组成的委员会将致力于撤销这份报告，并将它已经对以色列造成的“极大伤害”降低到最小。**++Mr. Frank’s name did come up repeatedly as a villain in the crisis, and not just in the context of the Dodd-Frank financial reform bill, which Republicans want to repeal.**++在这次危机之中，弗兰克先生的名字作为恶人的确反复出现，不光是在共和党人要废除的多德-弗兰克金融改革法案的背景下出现。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1531', 'repel', '[rɪpɛl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repel', '{vt.}++击退；抵挡住；驱除：**++拒绝；排斥：**++不接待；不理睬：**++使厌恶；使反感；使(昆虫等)不敢接近：**++抗；防：**{vi.}++抵制；排斥：**++引起反感：**', '++In an attempt to disgust and repel these vile oppressors, I once again induced myself to vomit on their favourite chair ...**++为了恶心并击退这些可恶的统治者们，我又在他们最喜欢的椅子上吐了个一塌糊涂......**++Why This Works: Many plants – including the ones listed – give off a strong scent to repel ants and other insects in the wild, and it works just as well in your home.**++为何如此：许多的植物——包括我上面列的单子——可以发出强烈的令蚂蚁和其它野外的昆虫害怕的气味，这样可以击退它们，不过对你的家庭却无害。**++This would have brought the largely lawless areas near Afghanistan into mainstream society or helped them see it as in their interest to repel militants.**++本来这些会有助于阿富汗附近基本上无法无天的地区融入主流社会，或者帮助他们发现抵制武装分子是符合他们的利益的。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1532', 'replace', '[rɪples]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=replace', '{vt.}++把…放回原处，放回：**++代替，取代：**++替换；更换：**++归还；赔：**', '++Please replace the books after reading.**++看完书后请将书放回原处。**++You can swap out one system and replace it with another.**++您可以交换一个系统并且用其它的系统替换它。**++However, this will replace all of your work in this project, so backup anything you want to keep.**++不过，这将替换您在此项目中的所有工作，所以，请备份您需要保存的任何内容。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1533', 'replacement', '[rɪplesmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=replacement', '{n.}++归还；复位；复职**++顶替；更换**++代替者；代替物**++取代；置换；移位**++补充兵员**++[亦作 metasomatism]【地质学】交代(作用)**', '++Replacement of sugar in your diet can be difficult.**++在你的饮食中更换糖肯定是困难的。**++Next you determine the replacement costs of each tangible asset for a specified period of time (usually a year).**++接下来您确定每种有形资产在特定时期内（通常为一年）的更换成本。**++It is similar to Listing 7 in that it replaces a fixed string, but the trick is that the replacement itself for the fixed string becomes the fixed string the next time.**++它与清单 7 的相似之处在于它替换了固定字符串，但诀窍在于替代该固定字符串的字符串本身在下次替换时又成了固定字符串。**');
