insert into CET6WordBook values ('1812', 'sullen', '[sʌlən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sullen', '{adj.}++愠怒的，不高兴的，闷闷不乐的**++愁眉不展的，苦闷的**++沮丧的**++(声音等)沉闷的**++(颜色、色彩等)不鲜明的，阴暗的**++阴沉的**++(流水等)缓慢的；停滞的**++[废语]邪恶的，不吉利的**{n.}++[用复数][古语]愠怒，生气，情绪消沉**', '++Heathcliff, dear! you should not be sullen now.**++希刺克厉夫，亲爱的！ 现在你不该沉着脸。**++And I felt just like a sullen new mom, not ready for her role.**++并且我就像一个闷闷不乐的新妈妈，来不及应付她的角色。**++Henry was a neat man, his lab coat clean, what remained of his hair combed and parted precisely; he was quiet, but said enough not to seem sullen.**++亨利是一个整洁的男士，他的实验工作服很干净，他的头发梳理过，而且整齐的分开；他很安静，话多的刚好让他不会显得阴沉。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1813', 'summary', '[sʌməri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summary', '{adj.}++总结性的，概括的，概述的**++简明的，扼要的**++即时的，即刻的**++简化了的；草率的**++【法律】简易的，即决的**++[废语]大体上的，不详细的**++[废语]最高的，顶点的**{n.}++总结，概略，摘要，一览**++[废语]结局；顶点**', '++His summary prosifies the poem.**++他的摘要把诗散文化了。**++Then, write a quick summary of the conversation and why youare perfect for the job.**++然后，写一个谈话的快速摘要以及为什么你非常适合这份工作。**++The Controller Summary provides a list of all the controller actions in an application in one report.**++控制器概要提供了一份报告，列出了应用程序中所有的控制器行为。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1814', 'summit', '[sʌmɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summit', '{n.}++最高峰，极顶，最高点**++极度，极点**++(成就、抱负等的)顶峰，巅峰**++(政府、外交等的)最高官阶，首脑；最高级会谈**++【数学】锥顶，锥体顶点**{adj.}++最高级的，国家元首之间的**{vi.}++参加最高级会谈，参加峰会，参加首脑会晤：**++达到性欲高潮**{vt.}++使达到顶峰**', '++All their attempts at reaching the summit failed.**++他们攀登顶峰的一切尝试都失败了。**++But are these the summit of our values, of our aspirations of society?**++但这些是我们的价值观、我们对社会的抱负的顶点吗？**++Should you reach the summit you would have only one desire, and that to descend and be with those who dwell in the deepest valley.**++一旦你登上顶峰，你就只有一个愿望，那就是往下走入最深的峪谷里，和那里的人民一同生活。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1815', 'summon', '[sʌmən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summon', '{vt.}++召唤;召来(常与 away, to 或 from连用)：**++【法律】传唤，传讯：**++号召；召集：**++鼓起，激起，使振作(常与 up 连用)：**++要求，请求；要…投降：**', '++Parliament has powers to introduce and pass legislation, summon and impeach ministers or the president.**++议会拥有提出和通过法律、召集弹劾内阁成员或总统的权力。**++Her magnanimity provoked his tears: he wept wildly, kissing her supporting hands, and yet could not summon courage to speak out.**++她的宽宏大量惹起他的眼泪；他发狂地哭着，吻她那扶着他的手，却还不能鼓起勇气说出来。**++Yet we are still heirs to a noble struggle for freedom. And now we must summon all of our might and moral suasion to meet the challenges of a new age.**++然而我们依然是为争取自由而战的崇高使命的继承者，我们必须召唤我们所有的力量和道义的呼声应对新时代的各种挑战。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1816', 'superb', '[/suːpɜːrb/]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superb', '{adj.}++极好的，最佳的；杰出的，优秀的**++华丽的，华美的，高贵的；壮丽的；庄重的**++宏伟的**++极度的，非常的**++[废语]傲慢的，骄傲的**', '++The audience was fascinated by their superb performance.**++他们的精彩表演使观众看得入了迷。**++The ancient Mayan city of Palenque, with its superb jungle setting and exquisite architecture and decoration, is one of the marvels of Mexico.**++帕伦克这座古老的玛雅古城，凭借其华丽的丛林和高雅典建筑和装潢，成为了墨西哥的一个奇迹。**++Below you can see some examples of thunderstorms and some superb supercells.**++下面你将看到一些雷暴和极炫的超雷雨胞例子。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1817', 'superficial', '[,supɚfɪʃl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superficial', '{adj.}++表面的，外部的；外表的**++表皮的**++表面上的；表面性的**++肤浅的，浅薄的**++草率的，粗略的**++微不足道的**++面的，面积的，平方的**{n.}++[the superficial]浅薄的人;表面文章**++[用复数]表面，外表；外部**', '++Happily, there was no apparent discomfort to any of the animals, although therewere some changes in pigmentation and superficial damage to the skin.**++令人高兴的是，虽然有某些色素沉着的改变和皮肤表面的损伤，这些动物没有出现明显的不适。**++The only problem is that you have no system to what you do, you shadow them and copy the superficial parts of their life and get exhausted doing it.**++问题是你对自己所做的没有一个系统的整体概念。 你只是跟随模仿了他们生活中表面的一部分，最终只会感到疲惫。**++Filial piety should not be expressed via superficial “performance”, but via children’s genuine care and love for their parents.**++孝顺不应该通过表面的“表演”来表现，而是应该通过孩子们对父母真正的关爱来表达。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1818', 'superiority', '[su,pɪrɪɔrəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superiority', '{n.}++优越(性)；优势；上等，优良，优秀；上位，上级**++【苏格兰法律】(封建主的)土地权益**', '++She was prepossessed with the notion of her own superiority.**++她满脑子充满着优越感。**++Well, in the quest for data storage superiority, a group of scientists from the University of Southampton say they@ve found forever and they, too, would like to share it with you.**++然而，在研究优越性的数据存储过程中，一组来自于南安普敦大学的科学家们表示他们已经找到了永久，同样，他们也愿意和你一起分享。**++Ultimately, our aim should not be to assert the superiority of the physical world over the virtual, but to make them work together.**++最终，我们的目标不应是证明实体世界相对于虚拟世界的优越性，而是让它们和谐共存。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1819', 'supersonic', '[,supɚsɑnɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supersonic', '{adj.}++超声速的，超音速的**++可超声速的，能超音速的**++[口语]特快的，极快的；极好的，令人兴奋的**++(声波、振动等)超声频的； **++由超声波引起(或产生)的**++利用超声波的**{n.}++超声频；超声波**++[口语]超音速飞机**', '++The asteroid blew up with the energy of the largest hydrogen bombs ever detonated on Earth, vaporizing the desert and unleashing deadly supersonic winds for many miles.**++小行星爆炸释放的能量相当于地球上有史以来最大的氢弹爆炸的能量总和，使沙漠蒸发，并在许多英里内引起了致命的超音速风。**++Supersonic flights are allowed only over water—and are thus limited to connecting wealthy cities separated by an ocean—because sonic booms can damage things and annoy people on the ground.**++超音速的飞机只允许在水上飞行，这样就只限于往返于被海洋隔开的富裕的国家——因为声震可以毁坏东西和给在地面上的人产生噪声。**++A companion research effort looked at concepts for a new generation of supersonic transport aircraft capable of meeting NASA@s noise, emissions and fuel efficiency goals for 2030.**++一项合作研究成果着眼于新一代超音速运输飞行器的概念，以满足NASA为2030世代设定的噪音、排放和燃油效率目标。**');
insert into CET6WordBook values ('1820', 'superstition', '[,supɚstɪʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superstition', '{n.}++迷信**++迷信行为(或状态)**++迷信制度**++(宗教)惶恐**++盲目的信仰**', '++There are several possible origins for this superstition.**++关于这个迷信有一些可能的起源。**++His mind was besotted with fear,ignorance and superstition.**++他的头脑被恐惧、愚昧和迷信所麻痹。**++Science is but one form of rationality, while religion is the most common form of superstition… If the history of science shows us anything, it is that we get nowhere by calling our ignorance @God@.**++科学是唯一的理性形式，而宗教是最常见的迷信形式……如果说科学史告诉了我们什么，那就是：把我们的无知称为‘上帝’不会有任何用处。**');
